com.google.gxp.compiler.schema
Class ElementValidator

java.lang.Object
  com.google.gxp.compiler.schema.ElementValidator
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public final class ElementValidator
extends Object
implements Serializable

Schema component which represents an XML element. SchemaParser creates these out of <element> elements.

Each ElementValidator corresponds to a single type of element in the output, but may be used to validate an arbitrary number of elements of that type. For example, one instance of ElementValidator could be used to validate all XHTML <img> elements.

ElementValidators are retrieved via Schema.getElementValidator(String).

Parameters:
tagName - name of the element.
flags - the set of flags which are enabled for this attribute.
innerContentType - the MIME "content type" of the element's body, or null if the element does not cause a content type change.
docTypes - DocTypes this ElementValidator allows to be referenced in this element with the gxp:doctype attribute.
attrs - AttributeValidators for all of the attribute allowed in this element.
